## Phase 5: Integration & Testing (1 week)

### 5.1 End-to-End Offline Dispatch

**Test path:**
```bash
cd /home/administrator/openclaw/skills/garden-conversation

# Full offline dispatch
python3 dispatch-step.py --offline --email mdcscry@yahoo.com --stage weather
python3 dispatch-step.py --offline --email mdcscry@yahoo.com --stage dialogue
python3 dispatch-step.py --offline --email mdcscry@yahoo.com --stage art
python3 dispatch-step.py --offline --email mdcscry@yahoo.com --stage masthead
```

**Success criteria:**
- Each stage completes without Anthropic calls
- Dialogue contains character-specific voice
- Prose refinement preserves character voice
- Final output is coherent and usable

### 5.2 Comparative Testing (Offline vs Online)

**Test matrix:**
| Stage | Online model | Offline model | Quality parity? | Voice preservation? |
|-------|---|---|---|---|
| Dialogue (Harry) | claude-sonnet | gemma2 | | |
| Dialogue (Muso) | claude-sonnet | gemma2 | | |
| Haiku refinement | claude-haiku | gemma2/mistral | | |
| Sonnet refinement | claude-sonnet | mistral/neural-chat | | |
| AFD summary | claude-sonnet | mistral/neural-chat | | |

**Run same 5 test cases online and offline, compare:**
- Word count
- Character voice (qualitative)
- Tone preservation
- Error rates

### 5.3 Fallback Logic (Optional Phase 5b)

**If offline quality is marginal:** Add graceful fallback:
```python
try:
    result = call("character-offline", ..., prompt, 90)
    if looks_empty_or_bad(result):
        result = call("character", ..., prompt, 90)  # fallback to online
except:
    result = call("character", ..., prompt, 90)
```

**Decision:** Only implement if offline models consistently underperform.

